==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Synecdochical
<hw>Syn`ec*doch"ic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Expressed by
synecdoche; implying a synecdoche.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Isis is used for Themesis by a <qex>synecdochical</qex> kind of
speech, or by a poetical liberty, in using one for another.</q>
<rj><qau>Drayton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Synecdochically</ent>⟦br⟧
